description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Provide the very best care, for every Patient, every day…..&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Position: &lt;/strong&gt;Band 6 Senior Anaesthetic Practitioner&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;West Hertfordshire Hospitals NHS Trust provides acute healthcare services to a population of approximately half a million people living in West Hertfordshire and the surrounding areas. As an employer of over 4000 people we are one of the biggest employers in the area and see around one million patients each year. Every day in our hospitals, staff go to extraordinary lengths to provide exceptional care and support for our patients, as well as their families and friends.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will be responsible as the Band 6 team leader in anaesthetics caring for patients undergoing anaesthetic intervention in all specialities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will require leadership and motivation of the multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunities in theatres&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CPD opportunities including post registration paediatric courses&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent team working in a multi professional environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Mentorship opportunities supporting the diverse professions working in the operating department&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supported induction and preceptorship programmes with skills and competency packages relevant to the specialist area of surgical practice.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Tanya McIntyre- Theatres Ext: 7122&lt;/p&gt;
